00:08:48.970 --> 00:08:52.280
I'm going to talk about how
historians look at time,

00:08:52.280 --> 00:08:55.896
historians of modern Europe
or European historians,

00:08:55.896 --> 00:08:58.260
this'll give us two different perspectives

00:08:58.260 --> 00:09:00.317
on how historians look at time,

00:09:00.317 --> 00:09:04.010
I'm gonna focus really on
three issues that European

00:09:04.010 --> 00:09:05.660
historians have looked at

00:09:05.660 --> 00:09:09.670
in a broad range of European history.

00:09:09.670 --> 00:09:14.670
The first is the technology
of time and that's the

00:09:14.780 --> 00:09:19.780
transition from bells to
clocks to watches and so on

00:09:19.940 --> 00:09:24.000
which has a long history in
the west and all over the world

00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:25.657
and that's one thing that people look at

00:09:25.657 --> 00:09:27.690
and we'll see how that
comes back at the end.

00:09:27.690 --> 00:09:31.060
The second is sort of the
metaphysical notion of history.

00:09:31.060 --> 00:09:33.030
With the decline of the
Roman Empire and the rise

00:09:33.030 --> 00:09:34.350
of Christianity,

00:09:34.350 --> 00:09:36.820
Christian conceptions of
time kind of took over

00:09:36.820 --> 00:09:39.850
in the medieval west and
dominated western thought

00:09:39.850 --> 00:09:42.860
for a long, long time, the
easiest way of seeing that

00:09:42.860 --> 00:09:45.600
is in the Bible as history,
there's an Old Testament

00:09:45.600 --> 00:09:48.382
and a New Testament, divided
by the coming of Christ

00:09:48.382 --> 00:09:51.110
and then with the prefiguring of the

00:09:52.190 --> 00:09:53.750
last judgment.

00:09:53.750 --> 00:09:56.930
That also opens up the
notion of a temporal

00:09:56.930 --> 00:09:59.830
versus the eternal, which was
as much on people's minds,

00:09:59.830 --> 00:10:02.460
the temporal, the post, after the fall,

00:10:02.460 --> 00:10:06.040
after Adam and Eve, men
and women were subject

00:10:06.040 --> 00:10:10.860
to all the vicissitudes of
life and subject to time.

00:10:10.860 --> 00:10:14.276
Whereas the eternal which
was the realm of God

00:10:14.276 --> 00:10:18.430
was without time or could be conceived of

00:10:18.430 --> 00:10:21.647
as endless time, time
after time after time.

00:10:21.647 --> 00:10:24.580
And the notion was of
course, the common notion was

00:10:24.580 --> 00:10:28.410
that that temporal age would
end at the last judgment,

00:10:28.410 --> 00:10:30.890
everything would be brought
together and some people

00:10:30.890 --> 00:10:34.150
would enjoy eternity, either
up above us or below us

00:10:34.150 --> 00:10:37.460
in heaven or in hell and that
was a kind of dominant theme.

00:10:37.460 --> 00:10:41.005
Another aspect of that
that was very important

00:10:41.005 --> 00:10:42.030
was that the teleological
aspect, people thought

00:10:42.030 --> 00:10:43.800
of history as having an end,

00:10:43.800 --> 00:10:46.560
it was guided towards something,

00:10:46.560 --> 00:10:47.950
things were either going to get better

00:10:47.950 --> 00:10:50.250
or they were going to get
worse, but they were always

00:10:50.250 --> 00:10:53.470
going to an end and that
end was the end of time

00:10:53.470 --> 00:10:57.300
so the Christian conception
of time in the medieval West

00:10:57.300 --> 00:11:00.470
was very dominant and had
really captured people's minds.

00:11:00.470 --> 00:11:02.530
It also captured people's
minds in another way,

00:11:02.530 --> 00:11:04.414
which I'll come back to,

00:11:04.414 --> 00:11:06.880
and then finally the third
conception is a social

00:11:06.880 --> 00:11:11.550
and economic conception of
time, how society patterns time

00:11:11.550 --> 00:11:15.460
or the vice versa, how time
patterns social activities

00:11:15.460 --> 00:11:19.117
and work, and those were two
very, very important issues

00:11:19.117 --> 00:11:21.310
and they are the issues
that really surround

00:11:21.310 --> 00:11:23.831
what became one of the
central and has been

00:11:23.831 --> 00:11:25.350
one of the central concerns
of European history

00:11:25.350 --> 00:11:28.850
for a long time and that is modernization

00:11:28.850 --> 00:11:31.710
or industrialization, now modernization,

00:11:31.710 --> 00:11:34.890
industrialization, is a process
that lasted for centuries

00:11:34.890 --> 00:11:38.160
in Europe, it is a process
that is still going on

00:11:38.160 --> 00:11:40.950
around the world, you can
think of it in simple terms

00:11:40.950 --> 00:11:44.801
as industry, factories,
trade, globalization,

00:11:44.801 --> 00:11:47.890
but more importantly from our standpoint

00:11:47.890 --> 00:11:50.530
here in this group, it also requires

00:11:50.530 --> 00:11:54.240
a radical restructuring
of time, of movement

00:11:54.240 --> 00:11:57.700
from preindustrial to
post industrial time.

00:11:57.700 --> 00:12:00.650
And those are two radically
different regimes.

00:12:00.650 --> 00:12:03.230
In order to show you how
radically different they were

00:12:03.230 --> 00:12:07.860
in the European west, I'll
refocus on, to begin with,

00:12:07.860 --> 00:12:11.960
preindustrial time, agrarian
time, the time dominated

00:12:11.960 --> 00:12:14.230
by the work of the fields, the work that

00:12:14.230 --> 00:12:18.280
the majority, the vast
majority, 99, 95, 99%

00:12:18.280 --> 00:12:22.073
of the population enjoyed or
worked in during their lives

00:12:22.073 --> 00:12:26.130
so it's that early aspect
that I want to think about

00:12:26.130 --> 00:12:29.603
and when you think about agrarian time,

00:12:29.603 --> 00:12:32.610
you have to think about
day time because night

00:12:32.610 --> 00:12:35.820
was absolutely dark and the possibility

00:12:35.820 --> 00:12:38.725
of falling into a cesspool,
stepping on a plow,

00:12:38.725 --> 00:12:41.850
getting rolled over by a
cart was all too common

00:12:41.850 --> 00:12:44.670
so you didn't go out after
dark, you were too poor,

00:12:44.670 --> 00:12:47.680
likely, to have candles even,
so most of the European West

00:12:47.680 --> 00:12:50.663
was really dark, so we're
talking about daytime

00:12:50.663 --> 00:12:53.971
and daytime was structured by work.

00:12:53.971 --> 00:12:56.750
The way in which you organized your day,

00:12:56.750 --> 00:12:58.600
the way in which you
thought about your day

00:12:58.600 --> 00:13:01.030
was according to the tasks you did.

00:13:01.030 --> 00:13:04.573
Now how many of you are horse racing fans?

