Eighth of a mile, well,
that's almost correct,

00:13:15.600 --> 00:13:18.460
it's the distance that
a plow team could go

00:13:18.460 --> 00:13:21.110
in a straight line before
it had to turn around

00:13:21.110 --> 00:13:23.600
and come back again to
plow the other side.

00:13:23.600 --> 00:13:26.393
That's where, it's a furrow long.

00:13:27.270 --> 00:13:28.610
Now.

00:13:28.610 --> 00:13:32.470
Given that, and given that
several furrows make an acre,

00:13:32.470 --> 00:13:34.043
how big is an acre?

00:13:38.600 --> 00:13:40.512
Oh, God, you're so post industrial.

