00:25:35.838 --> 00:25:40.250
Islam as some of you know was
born in 7th century Arabia.

00:25:40.250 --> 00:25:43.550
It's a area that's
populated by pagans, Jews,

00:25:43.550 --> 00:25:45.760
Zoroastrians, and Christians.

00:25:45.760 --> 00:25:50.650
And to differentiate
itself in this environment,

00:25:50.650 --> 00:25:55.650
Islam thoroughly and
radically redefined time.

00:25:55.820 --> 00:25:59.750
For preislamic Arabs,
time and the Arabic word

00:25:59.750 --> 00:26:02.394
or an Arabic word for
time, I should say, is

00:26:02.394 --> 00:26:05.229
(speaks foreign language),
for preislamic Arabs,

00:26:05.229 --> 00:26:08.930
(speaks foreign language) was
a cosmic force of its own.

00:26:08.930 --> 00:26:11.660
It controlled what we
might say is transient

00:26:11.660 --> 00:26:16.260
earthly happiness, it
ushered an inevitable death,

00:26:16.260 --> 00:26:19.450
and we see an allusion
to this kind of view

00:26:19.450 --> 00:26:23.178
in a Koranic verse that says,
they say there is nothing

00:26:23.178 --> 00:26:26.980
but the life of this
world, we die and we live

00:26:26.980 --> 00:26:29.950
and nothing destroys us but time.

00:26:29.950 --> 00:26:34.540
So in contrast to this,
Islam imposed or asserted

00:26:34.540 --> 00:26:37.700
a theocentric worldview,
a view that there was

00:26:37.700 --> 00:26:41.950
a monotheistic omnipotent
God who was the ultimate

00:26:41.950 --> 00:26:45.030
cause of all aspects of his creation

00:26:45.030 --> 00:26:48.173
and that is referenced in the second

00:26:48.173 --> 00:26:50.760
report that I have there, it's attributed

00:26:50.760 --> 00:26:53.710
to the prophet Muhammad,
in addition to this

00:26:53.710 --> 00:26:56.886
theocentric view or
alongside it, I should say,

00:26:56.886 --> 00:27:00.960
there is this notion of an afterlife,

00:27:00.960 --> 00:27:04.880
so Scott Waugh alluded
to it a little while ago,

00:27:04.880 --> 00:27:09.880
but essentially what Islam does
is extend the time horizon,

00:27:10.340 --> 00:27:14.640
if you will, of a believer to just

00:27:14.640 --> 00:27:17.610
this is not, it's not just
the life of this world,

00:27:17.610 --> 00:27:22.010
but there is an afterlife
to follow and Islam also

00:27:22.010 --> 00:27:27.010
preached the idea that faith
and actions were ultimately

00:27:27.410 --> 00:27:30.060
determinants of one's
destiny in the hereafter

00:27:30.060 --> 00:27:33.760
and not just the passage
of time that would control

00:27:33.760 --> 00:27:37.490
one's happiness or sorrow.

00:27:37.490 --> 00:27:41.755
Now alongside what I call a
cosmological reconfiguration,

00:27:41.755 --> 00:27:46.755
or as part of it, Islam
introduced a new calendar.

00:27:47.380 --> 00:27:50.250
Most of the communities of that time

00:27:51.180 --> 00:27:55.120
adhered to what we might
call a loony solar calendar,

00:27:55.120 --> 00:27:59.480
right, a lunar or solar calendar
that was roughly calibrated

00:27:59.480 --> 00:28:03.592
to the seasons, so I
mean, for us, in the north

