But also at the same time,
my father would teach me

00:42:31.012 --> 00:42:35.850
about the obsession of the
Maya with time in general

00:42:35.850 --> 00:42:39.263
and specifically about the
calendars in astronomy.

00:42:40.300 --> 00:42:43.660
How they used three separate
calendars and they were

00:42:43.660 --> 00:42:46.830
connected in three cycles
because they were cyclical

00:42:46.830 --> 00:42:50.550
calendars, how the Maya
calendar system was not just

00:42:50.550 --> 00:42:54.500
a method to track various celestial cycles

00:42:54.500 --> 00:42:57.085
but it was a complex
system used to establish

00:42:57.085 --> 00:43:01.020
which of the many gods
were ruling at each moment

00:43:01.020 --> 00:43:04.786
in their lives, the gods
were constantly creating,

00:43:04.786 --> 00:43:09.570
controlling, renewing the
world and all of the beings

00:43:09.570 --> 00:43:14.570
within it, so there was a
fluid cyclical map of creation,

00:43:14.920 --> 00:43:19.660
a making and unmaking, a
making and unmaking, and making

00:43:19.660 --> 00:43:23.610
and unmaking of all existence continually.

00:43:23.610 --> 00:43:26.710
So that sense of time
was so instilled in me

00:43:26.710 --> 00:43:30.951
that it kind of, the idea of linear time,

00:43:30.951 --> 00:43:34.343
I've had such a hard
time entering my brain.

00:43:35.460 --> 00:43:38.740
There was a time that I
